\lim_{x\to\frac{\pi}{2}}(\sin x)^{\tan x}
y=(\sin x)^{\tan x}
\log y=\tan x\log(\sin x)=\frac{\log(\sin x)}{\cot x}
x\to \pi/2
\log(\sin x)\to 0
\cot x\to 0
\lim_{x\to \pi/2}\frac{\log(\sin x)}{\cot x}=\lim_{x\to \pi/2}\frac{\cos x}{\sin x(-\csc^2 x)}=\lim_{x\to \pi/2}\frac{\cos x}{-\sin x}=0
\Rightarrow \log y\to 0, \text{as}, x\to \pi/2
\Rightarrow  y\to \exp^0, \text{as}, x\to \pi/2
\Rightarrow  y\to 1, \text{as}, x\to \pi/2
f(t) = \left(1 - 2 \sin^2(t/2)\right)^{\frac1{2\sin^2(t/2)}}
g(t) = \cos(t) \tan(t/2)
a=0
2 \sin^2(t/2)\cot(t) =2\sin^2(t/2) \dfrac{\cos(t)}{\sin(t)} = 2\sin^2(t/2) \dfrac{\cos(t)}{2 \sin(t/2) \cos(t/2)} = \cos(t) \tan(t/2)
\lim_{t \to 0} f(t)
\lim_{y \to 0}(1-y)^{1/y} = \dfrac1e
